Here's the full program (`net11.0`, top-level statements):

```csharp
using System;
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase
};

string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{"Name":"Alice","Age":30}
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` — a built-in policy (added in .NET 9) that converts the lowercase constructor parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the serialized JSON. No custom naming policy needed.
